<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-651-998  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 651 998.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Sept 1 1989 v15 n18 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Welcome to the digital world. (special report)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Powell, Doug.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A proposed US National Research and Education Network is a key topossible global economic leadership.andP;  The network would take theform of a 3G-bps fiber optic infrastructure that would connect thedesktop digital environment with supercomputers, laboratories anddatabases.andP;  Proposed by Sen Al Gore of the US Science, Space andTechnology subcommittee, the $1.75 billion 'data superhighway'would eventually reach into the home with a fiber-optic-basedcombination of phone calls, high-definition television (HDTV)signals, computer service, movies and information services.andP;  Longrange planning calls for governments to invest in the fiber optictechnology that carries the potential to bring a consumerrevolution into the home.andP;  A proposal for a Canadian nationalnetwork called NRNet has been approved by the Treasury Board and acall for bids is now circulating.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     International CommunicationsFiber OpticsDigital CommunicationsGoals and ObjectivesNetworksConnectivity.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>